other_tests.findings: The appendix demonstrates wall thickening, periappendiceal stranding, and dilation to 14 mm. There is marked restricted diffusion associated with the appendix. There is free fluid around the appendix, the cecal tip, and within the pelvis. An adjacent ileocecal lymph node measures up to 9 mm. The remainder of the bowel loops appear within normal limits. The ovaries demonstrate normal follicular change. The uterus has an intrauterine pregnancy with an anterior placenta.
